TITLE: Defining User Entity with Many To Many Relation in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to define a User entity with a Many To Many relationship to Tags using annotations, including methods for managing the tags collection.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cycle/docs/blob/2.x/docs/en/relation/many-to-many.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use Cycle\Annotated\Annotation\Relation\ManyToMany;
use Cycle\Annotated\Annotation\Entity;

#[Entity]
class User
{
    // ...

    #[ManyToMany(target: Tag::class, through: UserTag::class)]
    protected array $tags;

    public function getTags(): array
    {
        return $this->tags;
    }

    public function addTag(Tag $tag): void
    {
        $this->tags[] = $tag;
    }

    public function removeTag(Tag $tag): void
    {
        $this->tags = array_filter($this->tags, static fn(Tag $t) => $t !== $tag);
    }
}
```

