TITLE: Creating a Manual Migration in PHP
DESCRIPTION: PHP class example of a manually created migration. It demonstrates how to define 'up' and 'down' methods for creating and dropping a table.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cycle/docs/blob/2.x/docs/en/database/migrations.md#2025-04-20_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
class MyMigrationMigration extends Migration
{
    /**
     * Create tables, add columns or insert data here
     */
    public function up()
    {
        $this->table('sample_table')
            ->addColumn('id', 'primary')
            ->addColumn('name', 'string')
            ->create();
    }

    /**
     * Drop created, columns and etc here
     */
    public function down()
    {
        $this->table('sample_table')->drop();
    }
}
```

