TITLE: Parsing joined query results with nested nodes
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to create a hierarchical data structure from a joined query by using RootNode and ArrayNode. The ArrayNode is used to define the relationship between parent and child records based on key mappings.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cycle/docs/blob/2.x/docs/en/advanced/node-parser.md#2025-04-20_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use Cycle\ORM\Parser;
use Cycle\Database\StatementInterface;

$root = new Parser\RootNode(
    ['id', 'balance'], ['id']
);

$root->joinNode('orders', new Parser\ArrayNode(
    ['id', 'user_id', 'total'], // column names
    ['id'],                     // primary keys
    ['user_id'],                // inner keys
    ['id']                      // outer keys (user.id)
));

foreach ($query->run()->fetchAll(StatementInterface::FETCH_NUM) as $row) {
    // start from 1st (0) column
    $root->parseRow(0, $row);
}
```

