TITLE: SQL Generated for Combined Load and With
DESCRIPTION: The SQL query generated when both filtering by and loading related entities. This creates separate aliases for the same table in different JOIN clauses.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cycle/docs/blob/2.x/docs/en/basic/relation.md#2025-04-20_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
SELECT "user"."id"                AS "c0",
       "user"."name"              AS "c1",
       "l_user_address"."id"      AS "c2",
       "l_user_address"."city"    AS "c3",
       "l_user_address"."user_id" AS "c4",
       "user_address"."id"        AS "c5",
       "user_address"."city"      AS "c6",
       "user_address"."user_id"   AS "c7"
FROM "users" AS "user"
         LEFT JOIN "addresses" AS "l_user_address"
                   ON "l_user_address"."user_id" = "user"."id"
         INNER JOIN "addresses" AS "user_address"
                    ON "user_address"."user_id" = "user"."id"
WHERE "user_address"."city" = 'New York';
```

