TITLE: Paginating User Select in Cycle ORM (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to paginate a simple User select query using Cycle ORM and Spiral Pagination. It creates a Select object, initializes a Paginator with 10 results per page, and applies pagination to the select query.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cycle/docs/blob/2.x/docs/en/advanced/pagination.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
$select = $orm->getRepository(User::class)->select()->orderBy('id', 'DESC');

// 10 results per page
$paginator = new \Spiral\Pagination\Paginator(10);
$paginator->paginate($select);

print_r($select->fetchAll());
```

